## Limitations

The evaluation is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the scope of government programs, which vary significantly across regions. Additionally, the impact of recent economic changes, such as the COVID-19 pandemic, on housing policies and their effectiveness was not fully explored due to the evolving nature of these developments. Further research could provide a more comprehensive understanding of the long-term impacts of government interventions in housing.